DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Upper Limit of Normal 3 Digit Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The 3 digit numeric value representing the upper level of the normal range of values for any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.
